What Are Keratin Bonded Hair Extensions?

Bonded hair extensions, often referred to as fusion hair extensions keratin bonds, or pre-bonded hair extensions, are one of the more sophisticated techniques for hair extensions. Bonded hair extensions differ from traditional hair extensions in that they come in individual strands rather than in wefts. As a result, you must attach each strand of the extension separately to completely cover the head. Each of these hair extensions have Keratin infused into or pre-bonded onto the tips of each strand. There is no glue needed for installation. Keratin, a naturally occurring protein that helps to build hair, attaches to your hair better and does less damage than traditional methods.

How Long Do Hair Extensions Last?

I am often asked this question and the quick answer is approximately 3 months. However, the truth is that there are various factors at play here. How long your hair extensions last will depend on a number of factors:

• Application – who and how well
• The hair quality is one of the most important factors. With virgin hair, lux quality you can use same hair for few years at least. 
• How often you wash your hair
• How quickly your own hair grows
• Amount of heat and stress applied (blowdrying, curling and straightening)
• How well you care for your hair extensions
• The products you use on the hair
• Your lifestyle (are you a gym-goer, swimmer, horse rider, police constable, cyclist and so on – as hats can irritate the scalp)
• Any medication you are taking (as some can increase hair shedding)
• If you touch and play with your extensions or bonds

But you must get correction every 3-4 months, for some even 2 months.

I WORK ON QUALITY, NOT QUANTITY!!! MY JEWELRY WORK TAKES TIME. 

Keratin bonded method can be installed on average between 4-6 hours. It is a piece by piece method where around 200-400 strands or more of hair that is tipped with keratin is melted and hardened to your own hair of about the same amount of strands so that the weight is evenly distributed to not cause tension on your own hair, which is must important). The strands can be custom sized to accomodate whether you have fine, medium, or thick hair.
We capsuling the hair by hand, one by one strands and most of the time our capsules are micro, which can take from 4-8 hours just to capsulate. 
We work on a quality, not quantity! This is a jewelry work, which takes time. If you do not have the time or patience to get your hair extensions installed perfectly, then we can't help you. Some places do the installation 2 times faster, but as you can imagine the quality is not the same.
